public class GameModel

updateHit

public int[] updateHit(comp102x.ColorImage footballImage,
                       int goalWidth,
                       int goalHeight,
                       int margin)
Updates the hit status of the goals and return the row and column for the hit goal if any. This method checks if the football image at the end of the shooting animation is completely within any goal image. If yes, the hit status of that goal image is updated to be true. The row number and column number of the goal is then returned. If no goal is hit, null is returned.

Parameters:
footballImage - the football image at the end of the shooting animation.
goalWidth - the width of a goal image.
goalHeight - the height of a goal image.
margin - the graphical separation between each goal image.
Returns:
a 1D array with the first element as the row and second element as the column of the hit goal. null is returned if not goal is hit.
